  "local_port": 60392,
  "remote_port": 443,
  "prompt": "How do I use WhatsApp on a PC?",
  "response": "Using WhatsApp on a PC can be accomplished in a couple of ways: through WhatsApp Web or the WhatsApp Desktop application. Here\u2019s how you can set up each:\n\n### WhatsApp Web\n1. **Open a Web Browser**: On your PC, open a web browser and go to [web.whatsapp.com](https://web.whatsapp.com/).\n\n2. **Open WhatsApp on Your Phone**:\n   - **For Android**: Open WhatsApp and tap on the three vertical dots (menu) on the top right, then select **Linked devices**.\n   - **For iPhone**: Open WhatsApp, go to **Settings**, and then tap on **Linked Devices**.\n\n3. **Link Device**:\n   - Tap on **Link a device**. This will open a QR code scanner within WhatsApp on your phone.\n\n4. **Scan QR Code**: \n   - Use your phone's camera to scan the QR code displayed on the WhatsApp Web page. This will sync your phone\u2019s WhatsApp with your PC.\n\n### WhatsApp Desktop App\n1. **Download the App**:\n   - Visit the [WhatsApp Download page](https://www.whatsapp.com/download/) on your PC.\n   - Download the appropriate version for your operating system (Windows or macOS).\n\n2. **Install the App**: \n   - Run the installer and follow the installation instructions.\n\n3. **Open the App**: \n   - Once installed, open the WhatsApp Desktop app.\n\n4. **Link Device**:\n   - Just like with WhatsApp Web, open WhatsApp on your phone and go to **Linked Devices**.\n   - Tap on **Link a device** to scan the QR code displayed in the WhatsApp Desktop app.\n\n### Tips\n- **Keep Your Phone Connected**: For both methods to work efficiently, your phone needs to stay connected to the internet.\n- **Stay Logged In**: You can choose to remain logged in on the PC by selecting the \"Keep me signed in\" option on the QR code scanning page.\n- **Security**: Always log out from shared or public computers after using WhatsApp Web or Desktop.\n\nBy following these steps, you should be able to use WhatsApp on your PC seamlessly for both personal and professional communication.",
